==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-hardening
<hw>Self`-hard"en*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Metal.)</fld>
<def>Designating, or pert. to, any of various steels that harden when
heated to above a red heat and cooled in air, usually in a blast of cold
air with moderate rapidity, without quenching. Such steels are alloys of
iron and carbon with manganese, tungsten and manganese, chromium,
molybdenum and manganese, etc. They are chiefly used as high-speed
steels.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Self`-hard"en*ed</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-heal</ent>⟦br⟧
